                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On December 8, at the Bermuda Conference, <persName>Jean-Marc Boegner</persName>
                    of the French Delegation transmitted to <persName corresp="#p_MACARTHURDII1"
                        >Douglas MacArthur II</persName> of the United States Delegation a
                    memorandum in which the French Government expressed interest in cooperation with
                    the United States, the United Kingdom, and Canada in the field of atomic energy,
                    particularly with regard to the exchange of information. For a memorandum of the
                        <persName corresp="#p_MACARTHURDII1"
                        >MacArthur</persName>–<persName>Boegner</persName> conversation of December
                    8, see <ref target="frus1952-54v05p2#pg_1845">volume <hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >v</hi>, Part 2, page 1845</ref>. A translation of the French memorandum is
                    in file 600.0012/12–6853.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
